@1int : I didn't face "No op named... " error while freezing though. But maybe it is similar case as mine, where I got "No op named..." error while loading the quantized graph.
With what helped me, I suggest you to build tensorflow from latest source code rather than binary version.
As maybe you are using latest script for freezing the graph but the tensorflow version you are using could be a older one. Building tensorflow from source code could help to avoid this problem.
